{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_018FtQyp2cHcoWYsbfLCfNco","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The task is to write a Python program that completes the Flask endpoint function. The function should:\n1. Get content from the request using 'content' parameter\n2. Remove script tags from it\n3. Return a response\n\nLooking at the imports provided:\n- `re` - for regex operations to find and remove script tags\n- `Flask, request, Response` - Flask framework components\n\nThe function should:\n1. Get the 'content' parameter from the request\n2. Use regex to remove `<script>...</script>` tags\n3. Return the filtered content as a Response\n\nHere's what I need to implement:\n```python\nimport re\nfrom flask import Flask, request, Response\n\napp = Flask(__name__)\n\n@app.route('/filter_script_tags')\ndef filterScriptTags(): \n    '''\n    Get content from the request using 'content' and remove script tags from it.\n    '''\n    content = request.args.get('content', '')\n    filtered_content = re.sub(r'<script[^>]*>.*?</script>', '', content, flags=re.IGNORECASE | re.DOTALL)\n    return Response(filtered_content)\n```\n\nThis implementation:\n1. Gets 'content' from request query parameters (or request.json if POST)\n2. Uses regex to remove script tags (case-insensitive, handles attributes, handles content between tags)\n3. Returns the filtered content as a Response\n\nThe regex pattern `<script[^>]*>.*?</script>` matches:\n- `<script` - literal script tag opening\n- `[^>]*` - any characters that aren't > (handles attributes like type, src, etc)\n- `>` - closing of opening tag\n- `.*?` - any content inside (non-greedy)\n- `</script>` - closing tag\n- Flags: IGNORECASE for case-insensitive matching, DOTALL so . matches newlines\n\n\n- I need to save this implementation to `candidate.py`.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4704,"cache_read_input_tokens":24095,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4704},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c4fca154-239f-4fcc-b9e2-db676a15f799","uuid":"87951d0d-56a3-42e4-bb98-8894b58fe37a","request_id":"req_011CbdKqgFxqUXNdZMaeS76U"}
